text: Hey, Warren. Guess what, I--
( mutters, laughs )

- What are you doing?
- Well, you know,

it's just little
corrective measures.
Seriously.

Our boy Jack has a bad case
of butterfingers.

He keeps dropping the ball
and costing us games,

so I figured I'd give him
a hand with his grip.
Ooh.
( laughs )

Well, in unrelated news,
my knee is looking good

and coach gave me the okay
to get back on the field.
Oh, captain, my captain.
That's great news, man.
Want to give me a hand?
I'll see you out there.
All right.
( Warren laughs )
( chuckles )

Dude, can you believe it?
It's tapioca again.
We need to talk.
Are you breaking up with me?

You didn't bust
your knee again, did you?

No, no. I'm fine.
I'm fine, but...

I think you should
apologize to Jack

and find a way
to make it right.
Oh, that's a good one.
I'm serious.

Who made you
the chief of police?

Come on, man.
Just do me this one solid.

I can't have this kind
of behavior on the team.

- It's bad for morale.
- What happened to you, man?

Did you break your
funny bone or something?
Come on. Just apologize.

- Or--
- Or what?

I'll tell it was you
and recommend he suspend you.

- You're kidding.
- No, I'm not.

It's my responsibility
to look out--
I'm sorry, you were saying?

- That's my locker!
- Oh, my gosh!
Man: Hey!
